# Pricing & Financial Policy

## Background pricing engine

Runs after technical spec is saved. Technician never sees prices during spec entry.

## Materials basis — Highest Purchase Price (not WAC)

Materials are always valued at the highest registered purchase price:

```
line_cost       = qty × highest_registered_purchase_price(item)
materials_total = Σ line_cost        # PricingRequest.computed_total
```

WAC is for **inventory valuation and financial reports only** — not for civilian quote building.

## Costing engine — modes → selling price becomes the quote

After adjustments, `PricingRequest.computed_total` (materials) is frozen, then a
configurable costing mode (`costing_modes` / `costing_components`, editable in
Admin → costing settings) is applied by `CostingEngine`:

```
component.amount = rate% × materials_total          # per configured component
components_total = Σ component.amount                # only when mode.has_components
total_cost       = materials_total + components_total
selling_price    = total_cost × (1 + profit_rate%)  # PricingRequest.selling_price
```

- `طرف صناعي` (`prosthetic_limb`): materials + components + profit.
- `الصرف السريع` (`quick_dispense`): materials + profit only (no components).
- No mode selected → `selling_price = materials_total` (no profit).

The frozen snapshot (mode, components JSON, total_cost, profit_rate,
`selling_price`) lives on `pricing_requests`. On confirm, **`selling_price`
becomes the issued `Quote.total`** (falling back to `computed_total` only when no
selling price is set). The legacy `OverheadCostingEngine` breakdown remains
**internal admin display only** and is never the patient/entity offer.
Contract-entity discount is applied for **display/print and AR posting**.

## Civilian financial flow

1. `PricingRequest` → admin approval → `Quote` with QR
2. Contract entity approval (OCR/scan) unlocks manufacturing
3. On delivery: post receivable to `ContractCompany` / debt ledger
4. Credit notes for partial/full rejection after delivery (`CreditNote`)

## Military financial flow

- Calculate full cost silently on pricing event
- No quote, no payment gate, no patient billing
- On delivery: accumulate cost to **sovereign / military debt** bucket for BI board 4

## Contract entities (`ContractCompany`)

- Civilian insurers, NGOs, etc. — normal AR/debt tracking
- Military sovereign entities — reporting-only debt, no payment demand

## BI financial metrics (board 4)

- Cumulative civilian cost by contract entity
- Aggregated military cost (sovereign)
- Net contract debts outstanding

Purchasing board (5): compare WAC vs highest purchase price per item for negotiation.
